# KubeJS & Minecraft Context
- Minecraft Version: 1.20.1 
- Mod Loader: Forge 
- KubeJS Version: 6.5 

# Syntax Rules
- DO NOT use the old `onEvent('recipetype', event => ...)` syntax.
- USE the new event system: `ServerEvents.recipes(event => ...)` or `StartupEvents.registry('item', event => ...)`.
- For item tags use: `ServerEvents.tags('item', event => ...)`
- Always prefer `event.remove({ id: '...' })` over removing by output where possible just to be safe.

# General Behavior
- When asking for scripts, always specify if it is a SERVER script (reloadable) or STARTUP script (requires restart).
- Consult the @KubeJS Wiki for any methods involving `Create` mod integration or complex NBT handling.